# ============================================================
# WORK CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: work
scope: work.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for work.

## policy_rules
Work policy constrains:
- who may assign work
- who may execute work
- which work may be visible
- which work requires review or approval
- how work history may be disclosed

## required_behavior
- assignment eligibility must be explicit
- executor eligibility must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- review/approval gates must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public opportunity summary
- executor-scoped detail
- operator-scoped detail
- reviewer-scoped detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow assignment only for valid authority
- allow execution only for valid scope
- allow review only for valid reviewer scope
- deny hidden role widening
- deny out-of-scope execution
- deny improper disclosure of work detail

## escalation_rules
If assignment authority,
executor eligibility,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the work path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- assignment policy is explicit
- execution policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- escalation rules are explicit
